      "fontFamily": 3,
      "text": "LIVER & DETOX\n• Modern food overloads liver: preservatives,\n  dyes, gums (xanthan, guar), stabilizers, seed oils\n• Volcanic water in CR may contain arsenic,\n  cyanide, mercury, lead → liver filters all of it\n• Signs of overloaded liver:\n   – flat belly AM, hard pouch by night\n   – afternoon crash, brain fog, want coffee\n   – dry/itchy skin or scalp (despite humidity)\n   – breakouts on face, shoulders, back\n   – bloated after every meal\n\nLIVER RENEW (her formula)\n• Oregon grape · milk thistle seed · yellow dock\n  · dandelion · burdock · red root\n• Dose: 1 cap, 1–3× daily, WITH meals\n• Energy returns in ~2 weeks\n• \"Everyone should take it daily\" (her words)\n\nDIET — \"eat the rainbow\"\n• Minimal ≠ good. Avry's eggs+avocado+beef\n  pattern misses B vitamins, vit C, riboflavins\n• Need leafy greens, deep dark greens, fruits\n• Variety prevents mineral/vitamin deficiency\n• Avoid preservatives, dyes, chemicals, gums\n• Her habits: kale sautéed w/ cranberries +\n  parmesan, yogurt + berries + granola + cacao,\n  frozen blueberries OK, lasagna OK, freezer stew\n\nTINCTURE / EXTRACTION (her process)\n• Vodka 35–40% can't pull terpenes\n• Need 96–98% alcohol for full extraction\n• Operating range: 60–65% (dilute high-proof)\n• In US: Everclear (200 proof, 100%) +\n  distilled water + hydrometer\n• In CR: can't buy → she distills her own\n• Her still: cane sugar mash → yeast ferment\n  to 4% → distillation w/ glass+copper reflux\n  column → high ABV output\n• Alcohol vapor at 174°F, water at 200°F+\n• Workshop on distillation? \"No, too long,\n  too dangerous, can't get a still in CR\"\n\nLUNAR FARMING (her core operating system)\n• EVERY task has its own lunar window:\n   – Seed starting: ~19th–26th of cycle\n   – Pruning for bushier: 17th–25th\n   – Rooting cuts: 1st–13th\n   – Cuttings: 1st–8th\n   – Air layering: 24th–28th\n• Full moon + new moon (and ±2 days) = REST\n   never plant or cut, plants will struggle\n• Side-by-side cut tests prove it:\n  right-time cuts root fast, wrong-time cuts\n  struggle for weeks\n• \"Every farmer who has lived here always knows.\"\n• Catherine sent her lunar calendar via WhatsApp\n\nSEED SAVING (workshop coming June 2026)\n• Tomatoes: squeeze seeds + water in jar →\n  ferment 3–4 days till seeds sink and smells\n  fermenty → strain → wash → dry till crisp\n• Same for papayas\n• Fermenting removes germination-inhibitor gel\n• Bougainvillea cuttings: scrape bark bottom +\n  rooting hormone + nutrient potting mix\n• \"Pega pega\" = local cutting-fence technique\n\nSOIL (her raised-bed recipe)\n• Compost · sand · charcoal · rice hulls\n  · coconut coir · dirt · composted manure\n• Massive dump-truck loads, all mixed well\n• \"Amend the soil. Make it the best it can be.\n  Otherwise stuff won't grow, gets compacted,\n  washes away in rain.\"\n\nGUANACASTE CLIMATE\n• 100°F dry season, Dec 15 → Apr 15, no rain\n• Must irrigate everything during dry\n• Rainy season: corrugated plastic roof needed\n• Don't start new seeds in rainy (except trees)\n• Mold + fungus risk in rain → airflow critical\n• Costa Rica = 5 biospheres incl. snow (Chirripó)\n• Central valley = ideal grow-everything zone\n  (cooler, consistent rain, broccoli, carrots)\n• OSA = 450 in/yr rain, too wet for most crops\n• Work hours: 5–7 AM, evening watering only\n  (after 7 AM too hot/buggy/sweaty)\n\nFRUIT TREES on her farm (40+ kinds)\n• Grapefruit, orange, tangerine, papaya, pineapple\n• Pineapples regrow from twisted-off tops in water\n• Plant dies after one fruit, top makes the next\n\nSPECIFIC PLANTS\n• MORINGA = highest natural concentration of\n  vitamins + minerals (\"multivitamin tree\")\n  → grows in CR · eat leaf in salads (bitter)\n  → watch Discovery Channel YouTube doc\n• NONI tree (cutting example)\n• VETIVER grass = deep roots, anti-landslide\n• PAPAYA fruit = vit A + beta carotene (great)\n  seeds = arsenic + anti-parasitic but TOXIC\n  → her view: don't use as parasite cleanse\n\nWATER / WELLS\n• Permits required for legal wells in CR\n• Hand-dug or illegal Sunday-drilled common\n• Water access = critical infrastructure decision\n\nPOLLINATORS\n• Must plant flowers (Florida, Jamaica varieties\n  of flowering bushes) alongside food crops\n• Bees + butterflies don't show up on their own\n\nOTHER SUPPLEMENTS\n• \"Complete Mushrooms\" (the \"magic 16\")\n  → cardiovascular, immune, gut, lymphatic\n• Immunoberry (high zinc) — her AM routine\n• Longevity section in her shop\n\nMEDIA HYGIENE (her implicit advice)\n• \"YouTube + Instagram take a grain of truth\n  and make it dangerous\" (papaya-seeds-as-\n  parasite-cure example)\n• Vodka tincture YouTube advice = wrong\n• Always verify against actual practitioners",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LIVER & DETOX\n• Modern food overloads liver: preservatives,\n  dyes, gums (xanthan, guar), stabilizers, seed oils\n• Volcanic water in CR may contain arsenic,\n  cyanide, mercury, lead → liver filters all of it\n• Signs of overloaded liver:\n   – flat belly AM, hard pouch by night\n   – afternoon crash, brain fog, want coffee\n   – dry/itchy skin or scalp (despite humidity)\n   – breakouts on face, shoulders, back\n   – bloated after every meal\n\nLIVER RENEW (her formula)\n• Oregon grape · milk thistle seed · yellow dock\n  · dandelion · burdock · red root\n• Dose: 1 cap, 1–3× daily, WITH meals\n• Energy returns in ~2 weeks\n• \"Everyone should take it daily\" (her words)\n\nDIET — \"eat the rainbow\"\n• Minimal ≠ good. Avry's eggs+avocado+beef\n  pattern misses B vitamins, vit C, riboflavins\n• Need leafy greens, deep dark greens, fruits\n• Variety prevents mineral/vitamin deficiency\n• Avoid preservatives, dyes, chemicals, gums\n• Her habits: kale sautéed w/ cranberries +\n  parmesan, yogurt + berries + granola + cacao,\n  frozen blueberries OK, lasagna OK, freezer stew\n\nTINCTURE / EXTRACTION (her process)\n• Vodka 35–40% can't pull terpenes\n• Need 96–98% alcohol for full extraction\n• Operating range: 60–65% (dilute high-proof)\n• In US: Everclear (200 proof, 100%) +\n  distilled water + hydrometer\n• In CR: can't buy → she distills her own\n• Her still: cane sugar mash → yeast ferment\n  to 4% → distillation w/ glass+copper reflux\n  column → high ABV output\n• Alcohol vapor at 174°F, water at 200°F+\n• Workshop on distillation? \"No, too long,\n  too dangerous, can't get a still in CR\"\n\nLUNAR FARMING (her core operating system)\n• EVERY task has its own lunar window:\n   – Seed starting: ~19th–26th of cycle\n   – Pruning for bushier: 17th–25th\n   – Rooting cuts: 1st–13th\n   – Cuttings: 1st–8th\n   – Air layering: 24th–28th\n• Full moon + new moon (and ±2 days) = REST\n   never plant or cut, plants will struggle\n• Side-by-side cut tests prove it:\n  right-time cuts root fast, wrong-time cuts\n  struggle for weeks\n• \"Every farmer who has lived here always knows.\"\n• Catherine sent her lunar calendar via WhatsApp\n\nSEED SAVING (workshop coming June 2026)\n• Tomatoes: squeeze seeds + water in jar →\n  ferment 3–4 days till seeds sink and smells\n  fermenty → strain → wash → dry till crisp\n• Same for papayas\n• Fermenting removes germination-inhibitor gel\n• Bougainvillea cuttings: scrape bark bottom +\n  rooting hormone + nutrient potting mix\n• \"Pega pega\" = local cutting-fence technique\n\nSOIL (her raised-bed recipe)\n• Compost · sand · charcoal · rice hulls\n  · coconut coir · dirt · composted manure\n• Massive dump-truck loads, all mixed well\n• \"Amend the soil. Make it the best it can be.\n  Otherwise stuff won't grow, gets compacted,\n  washes away in rain.\"\n\nGUANACASTE CLIMATE\n• 100°F dry season, Dec 15 → Apr 15, no rain\n• Must irrigate everything during dry\n• Rainy season: corrugated plastic roof needed\n• Don't start new seeds in rainy (except trees)\n• Mold + fungus risk in rain → airflow critical\n• Costa Rica = 5 biospheres incl. snow (Chirripó)\n• Central valley = ideal grow-everything zone\n  (cooler, consistent rain, broccoli, carrots)\n• OSA = 450 in/yr rain, too wet for most crops\n• Work hours: 5–7 AM, evening watering only\n  (after 7 AM too hot/buggy/sweaty)\n\nFRUIT TREES on her farm (40+ kinds)\n• Grapefruit, orange, tangerine, papaya, pineapple\n• Pineapples regrow from twisted-off tops in water\n• Plant dies after one fruit, top makes the next\n\nSPECIFIC PLANTS\n• MORINGA = highest natural concentration of\n  vitamins + minerals (\"multivitamin tree\")\n  → grows in CR · eat leaf in salads (bitter)\n  → watch Discovery Channel YouTube doc\n• NONI tree (cutting example)\n• VETIVER grass = deep roots, anti-landslide\n• PAPAYA fruit = vit A + beta carotene (great)\n  seeds = arsenic + anti-parasitic but TOXIC\n  → her view: don't use as parasite cleanse\n\nWATER / WELLS\n• Permits required for legal wells in CR\n• Hand-dug or illegal Sunday-drilled common\n• Water access = critical infrastructure decision\n\nPOLLINATORS\n• Must plant flowers (Florida, Jamaica varieties\n  of flowering bushes) alongside food crops\n• Bees + butterflies don't show up on their own\n\nOTHER SUPPLEMENTS\n• \"Complete Mushrooms\" (the \"magic 16\")\n  → cardiovascular, immune, gut, lymphatic\n• Immunoberry (high zinc) — her AM routine\n• Longevity section in her shop\n\nMEDIA HYGIENE (her implicit advice)\n• \"YouTube + Instagram take a grain of truth\n  and make it dangerous\" (papaya-seeds-as-\n  parasite-cure example)\n• Vodka tincture YouTube advice = wrong\n• Always verify against actual practitioners",
