      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "text": "1.\n\"You can have a really healthy, clean diet\nand still have problems with your liver.\"\n\n2.\n\"You need to eat the rainbow. The more\ncolorful you can make your plate, the better.\"\n\n3.\n\"You can't pull a terpene out of a plant\nuntil it's 96, 98%. So you basically end up\ncomposting the things that you actually need.\"\n— on why vodka tinctures don't work\n\n4.\n\"Petroleum is a byproduct of pressure and\ntime, of organic matter at one time. But\nit's a toxic substance.\"\n— reframing the \"lifeblood of the earth\" myth\n\n5.\n\"Everybody that has ever lived anywhere here\nalways knows those things. Every farmer\nwill already know too.\"\n— on lunar planting being indigenous knowledge\n\n6.\n\"You only work from 5 to 7 in the morning.\nOtherwise after 7 o'clock it's too hot, too\nbuggy, too sweaty.\"\n— the daily rhythm of growing in Guanacaste\n\n7.\n\"If you do work on the full or new moon,\nthen you could start one cutting and one is\ngoing to root really fast and the other is\ngoing to be struggling. There's a lot of\nscience behind it.\"\n\n8.\n\"If you really wanted to live completely off\nthe land, grow everything, you would be up\ntowards the central valley.\"\n— location matters more than effort\n\n9.\n\"It's important to plant not only fruits\nand vegetables that you're going to eat,\nyou need to plant a bunch of flowery stuff\nthat the bees and the butterflies like.\"\n\n10.\n\"I would be all over taking the liver renew\nevery day. One in the morning, one at night.\nIt improves your liver function. So your liver\nis constantly overloaded with too much stuff\nand it helps repair the damage to your liver.\"\n\n11.\n\"Stop eating everything that has a preservative,\na dye, a chemical, a stabilizer, a gum.\nAll that stuff is your body's having to filter\nthat out.\"\n\n12.\n\"There's a lot of stuff on YouTubes and\nInstagrams and these little googly things…\nsomebody said something once because it has\na little tiny bit of truth, and so they're\nmaking it into something way bigger and\npotentially dangerous.\"\n— on papaya seeds as parasite cure\n\n13.\n\"Amend the soil. Make your soil the best\nthat it can be. Because if it isn't, then\nit's not going to grow.\"",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1.\n\"You can have a really healthy, clean diet\nand still have problems with your liver.\"\n\n2.\n\"You need to eat the rainbow. The more\ncolorful you can make your plate, the better.\"\n\n3.\n\"You can't pull a terpene out of a plant\nuntil it's 96, 98%. So you basically end up\ncomposting the things that you actually need.\"\n— on why vodka tinctures don't work\n\n4.\n\"Petroleum is a byproduct of pressure and\ntime, of organic matter at one time. But\nit's a toxic substance.\"\n— reframing the \"lifeblood of the earth\" myth\n\n5.\n\"Everybody that has ever lived anywhere here\nalways knows those things. Every farmer\nwill already know too.\"\n— on lunar planting being indigenous knowledge\n\n6.\n\"You only work from 5 to 7 in the morning.\nOtherwise after 7 o'clock it's too hot, too\nbuggy, too sweaty.\"\n— the daily rhythm of growing in Guanacaste\n\n7.\n\"If you do work on the full or new moon,\nthen you could start one cutting and one is\ngoing to root really fast and the other is\ngoing to be struggling. There's a lot of\nscience behind it.\"\n\n8.\n\"If you really wanted to live completely off\nthe land, grow everything, you would be up\ntowards the central valley.\"\n— location matters more than effort\n\n9.\n\"It's important to plant not only fruits\nand vegetables that you're going to eat,\nyou need to plant a bunch of flowery stuff\nthat the bees and the butterflies like.\"\n\n10.\n\"I would be all over taking the liver renew\nevery day. One in the morning, one at night.\nIt improves your liver function. So your liver\nis constantly overloaded with too much stuff\nand it helps repair the damage to your liver.\"\n\n11.\n\"Stop eating everything that has a preservative,\na dye, a chemical, a stabilizer, a gum.\nAll that stuff is your body's having to filter\nthat out.\"\n\n12.\n\"There's a lot of stuff on YouTubes and\nInstagrams and these little googly things…\nsomebody said something once because it has\na little tiny bit of truth, and so they're\nmaking it into something way bigger and\npotentially dangerous.\"\n— on papaya seeds as parasite cure\n\n13.\n\"Amend the soil. Make your soil the best\nthat it can be. Because if it isn't, then\nit's not going to grow.\"",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "baseline": 14
    },
