      "fontFamily": 3,
      "text": "THIS WEEK\n\n☐ Start Liver Renew\n   Visit Catherine's apothecary, get a bottle.\n   1 cap with breakfast, 1 with dinner. Add to\n   existing Complete Mushrooms regimen.\n   Notice: energy in ~2 weeks.\n\n☐ Pivot off the minimal diet\n   Add deep dark greens (kale, spinach),\n   variety of fruits, color on every plate.\n   Audit current week — where's the rainbow?\n\n☐ Read every yogurt + dairy label\n   Drop anything with xanthan/guar gum,\n   carrageenan, stabilizers. Same with sauces.\n\n☐ Save Catherine's WhatsApp lunar calendar\n   She sent one. Don't lose it.\n   Tag what's coming up in the next moon cycle.\n\n☐ Watch the Discovery Channel Moringa doc\n   YouTube search: \"Moringa Discovery channel\"\n   ~10 min. She specifically pointed.\n\n☐ Sign up for seed-saving workshop\n   June 2026. She has your contact.\n   Watch for email + flyers in town.\n\nNEAR-TERM (next 30 days)\n\n☐ Try Moringa\n   Buy from her shop OR find a tree locally.\n   Sauté leaves into salads, expect bitter.\n   Replace generic multivitamin.\n\n☐ Test soil thinking\n   Even before farming: where on current land\n   would raised beds go? Sun, drainage, rain.\n\n☐ Reach out to Catherine within 2 weeks of\n   her returning from family emergency.\n   Show up at the apothecary. Build the\n   relationship beyond this one conversation.\n\n☐ Stop using YouTube/IG for medical info\n   Verify everything against Catherine OR a\n   licensed practitioner OR primary research.\n\nLONGER TERM\n\n☐ Research central valley CR\n   If homestead is a real goal, location\n   matters more than effort.\n   Search: \"most food production Costa Rica\"\n\n☐ Apprentice question\n   She gets 5 asks/week for farm volunteering,\n   says no. What can you OFFER that makes\n   you different? (Not a fast follow.)\n\n☐ Distillation research\n   She won't teach it. YouTube it yourself.\n   Long-term: own still + Everclear from US trips.\n\n☐ Catherine collaboration angles\n   Workshop co-host? Recording her teaching?\n   Sacred Farm site improvements? Don't push,\n   listen first.\n\nNEXT-VISIT QUESTIONS\n(open the conversation with these)\n\n☐ Bottle size + cost on Liver Renew?\n   Does she ship to US? sacredfarm.com?\n\n☐ Specific plants for shade vs full sun\n   in your spot in Guanacaste?\n\n☐ How does she handle 100°F dry season\n   on the farm? Irrigation setup?\n\n☐ Local Nosara contractors who dig wells?\n\n☐ Her view on Ayurvedic + TCM herbs vs\n   Western herbalism? Compatible or competing?\n\n☐ What's her seed-saving curriculum cover\n   beyond tomatoes + papayas?\n\nROUTE TO OTHER AGENTS\n\n→ CHEF: \"eat the rainbow\" framework, kale\n  sauté recipe, freezer-meal stew template,\n  ingredients to avoid (gums, dyes, oils).\n\n→ TRAINER: liver health protocols, signs\n  of overloaded liver, recovery context\n  (afternoon crash = liver, not training).\n\n→ HOMEBASE/FARMER (FUTURE): lunar windows,\n  Guanacaste climate, soil amendments,\n  pollinator planting, central-valley\n  alternative location.\n\n→ GOD: lunar timing wisdom as indigenous\n  knowledge that science is catching up to.\n  The 5–7 AM rhythm as sacred-time.",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "THIS WEEK\n\n☐ Start Liver Renew\n   Visit Catherine's apothecary, get a bottle.\n   1 cap with breakfast, 1 with dinner. Add to\n   existing Complete Mushrooms regimen.\n   Notice: energy in ~2 weeks.\n\n☐ Pivot off the minimal diet\n   Add deep dark greens (kale, spinach),\n   variety of fruits, color on every plate.\n   Audit current week — where's the rainbow?\n\n☐ Read every yogurt + dairy label\n   Drop anything with xanthan/guar gum,\n   carrageenan, stabilizers. Same with sauces.\n\n☐ Save Catherine's WhatsApp lunar calendar\n   She sent one. Don't lose it.\n   Tag what's coming up in the next moon cycle.\n\n☐ Watch the Discovery Channel Moringa doc\n   YouTube search: \"Moringa Discovery channel\"\n   ~10 min. She specifically pointed.\n\n☐ Sign up for seed-saving workshop\n   June 2026. She has your contact.\n   Watch for email + flyers in town.\n\nNEAR-TERM (next 30 days)\n\n☐ Try Moringa\n   Buy from her shop OR find a tree locally.\n   Sauté leaves into salads, expect bitter.\n   Replace generic multivitamin.\n\n☐ Test soil thinking\n   Even before farming: where on current land\n   would raised beds go? Sun, drainage, rain.\n\n☐ Reach out to Catherine within 2 weeks of\n   her returning from family emergency.\n   Show up at the apothecary. Build the\n   relationship beyond this one conversation.\n\n☐ Stop using YouTube/IG for medical info\n   Verify everything against Catherine OR a\n   licensed practitioner OR primary research.\n\nLONGER TERM\n\n☐ Research central valley CR\n   If homestead is a real goal, location\n   matters more than effort.\n   Search: \"most food production Costa Rica\"\n\n☐ Apprentice question\n   She gets 5 asks/week for farm volunteering,\n   says no. What can you OFFER that makes\n   you different? (Not a fast follow.)\n\n☐ Distillation research\n   She won't teach it. YouTube it yourself.\n   Long-term: own still + Everclear from US trips.\n\n☐ Catherine collaboration angles\n   Workshop co-host? Recording her teaching?\n   Sacred Farm site improvements? Don't push,\n   listen first.\n\nNEXT-VISIT QUESTIONS\n(open the conversation with these)\n\n☐ Bottle size + cost on Liver Renew?\n   Does she ship to US? sacredfarm.com?\n\n☐ Specific plants for shade vs full sun\n   in your spot in Guanacaste?\n\n☐ How does she handle 100°F dry season\n   on the farm? Irrigation setup?\n\n☐ Local Nosara contractors who dig wells?\n\n☐ Her view on Ayurvedic + TCM herbs vs\n   Western herbalism? Compatible or competing?\n\n☐ What's her seed-saving curriculum cover\n   beyond tomatoes + papayas?\n\nROUTE TO OTHER AGENTS\n\n→ CHEF: \"eat the rainbow\" framework, kale\n  sauté recipe, freezer-meal stew template,\n  ingredients to avoid (gums, dyes, oils).\n\n→ TRAINER: liver health protocols, signs\n  of overloaded liver, recovery context\n  (afternoon crash = liver, not training).\n\n→ HOMEBASE/FARMER (FUTURE): lunar windows,\n  Guanacaste climate, soil amendments,\n  pollinator planting, central-valley\n  alternative location.\n\n→ GOD: lunar timing wisdom as indigenous\n  knowledge that science is catching up to.\n  The 5–7 AM rhythm as sacred-time.",
